    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-19T18:51:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-19T18:51:00-05:00" n="358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <head>358. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d358fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 411.9641/8–1955. Secret; Priority. Drafted in <gloss target="#t_PSA1"
                            >PSA</gloss>; approved in draft by <persName corresp="#p_SWJ1"
                            >Sebald</persName> and in final by <persName>Frederick E.
                            Nolting</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-19T18:51:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1955—6:51 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>626. Additional to penultimate sentence our 610.<note n="2" xml:id="d358fn2"
                        >Telegram 610, August 12, informed the Embassy of continuing efforts to
                        obtain a decision as to the availability of funds for <persName
                            corresp="#p_MR1">Magsaysay</persName>’s rural development program. It
                        also expressed apprehension that <persName corresp="#p_MR1"
                            >Magsaysay</persName> had not yet reached a final decision on his visit
                        to the United States since considerable advance planning was necessary for a
                        State visit. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 411.9641/8–1255)</note>
                </p>
                <p>As matter of principle and in practice Department wishes avoid associating grants
                    of US aid or loans with visits by Chiefs of State to US. Such visits should
                    stand on their own merits and association of aid with state or official visits
                    creates unfortunate precedents. Loans and grant assistance must be carefully
                    considered to determine if they are useful and appropriate and in conformity US
                    policy objectives.</p>
                <p>When asking <persName corresp="#p_MR1">Magsaysay</persName> for firm answer re
                    visit you may give him substance our thinking this subject and explain this does
                    not mean decision reached his proposal which still under consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
